field.description: Limit the response to specific field(s). See Metadata-field-filter.
field.name: fields

filter.description: Apply filter operations to the returned list of metadata. See Metadata-object-filter.
filter.name: filter

id.description: unique id of the element in the system.
id.name: id

mergeMode.description: Strategy for merging of objects when doing updates. REPLACE will just overwrite the propery with the new value provided, MERGE will only set the property if its not null (only if the property was provided).
mergeMode.name: mergeMode

order.description: Order the output using a specified order, only properties that are both persisted and simple (no collections, idObjects etc) are supported. iasc and idesc are case insensitive sorting.
order.name: order

page.description: Defines which page number to return.
page.name: page

pageSize.description: Defines the number of elements to return for each page.
pageSize.name: pageSize

paging.description: Indicates whether to return lists of elements in pages.
paging.name: paging

preheatCache.description: Turn cache-map preheating on/off. This is on by default, turning this off will make initial load time for importer much shorter (but will make the import itself slower). This is mostly used for cases where you have a small XML/JSON file you want to import, and don't want to wait for cache-map preheating.
preheatCache.name: preheatCache

strategy.description: Import strategy to use, see below for more information.
strategy.name: strategy

httpStatus.description: HTTP Status message for this response, see RFC 2616 (Section 10) for more information.

httpStatusCode.description: HTTP Status code for this response, see RFC 2616 (Section 10) for more information.

total.description: total number of items found by the request
